# Schola — Platform Overview (Synthesis)

## What Is It?

[[schola]] is a free, bilingual (English/Bahasa Malaysia) web-based career guidance platform for Malaysian secondary school students, built and operated by [[creador-foundation]]. It launched on **12 August 2024** and reached **320,000+ users** (200,000+ students) within months.

## The Problem It Solves

Malaysian students at the SPM stage systematically lack career knowledge when they need it most. A Creador Foundation study (n=1,000+) found 80% lack essential knowledge about their chosen career, 70% don't actively research options, and most only start planning *after* SPM. This is fundamentally an **information access gap**, not a talent gap — the core insight being "you can't be what you don't know."

## How It Works (Feature Set)

| Feature | Mechanism | Framework |
|---|---|---|
| Career Quiz | Personality quiz → career type card + job list | [[riasec-holland-codes]] |
| Subject-to-Job Match | Select 1–2 SPM subjects → matched career list | Student study data |
| Job Guides | 6-section per-job deep dive: description, salary, education path, expert tips, future outlook, quiz | Professional + official data |
| Gaji Goals Game | Pick 2 careers, compare salary growth and purchasing power over 10 years | Gamification |

## School Partnership Programme

Schola offers a structured **1.5-hour school workshop** (150+ requests received). The flow combines platform exploration with offline activities (career bingo, reality check exercise) and a feedback survey. Partners can incorporate their own activities.

## Strategic Positioning

- **Free** — explicitly positions against paid career counselling; democratises access
- **Evidence-based** — features grounded in student research and RIASEC framework
- **Bilingual** — removes language barrier for BM-dominant students
- **Self-directed** — students can use independently, without a counsellor

## Key Numbers (as of late 2024 / early 2025)

- 320,000+ total users; 200,000+ students
- 150+ school visit requests
- Launched: 12 August 2024

